---
title: Crispy Cauliflower and Squash Tacos with Yogurt Crema and a Chili Honey Drizzle
description: Dinnertime just got a seasonal upgrade with the addition of creamy butternut squash and roasted cauliflower inside these tortillas. The spices used to season the veggies bring lively flavors that ensure that this is one festive feast, especially when balanced with yogurt sauce and tangy lime. It’s so memorably tasty, we think you’ll still be raving about it for days and days.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/crispy-cauliflower-and-squash-tacos-77fed2b7.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/crispy-cauliflower-and-squash-tacos-3d57157e.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/crispy-cauliflower-and-squash-tacos-59ea110e30a03b4ba67302a2
nutrition:
  calories: 500 kcal
  fat: 23 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 71 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 17 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 910 mg
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 35 minutes
cuisine: North America
---

Wash and dry all produce. Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Spread out @cauliflower florets{10%ounce} on one #baking sheet{} and @butternut squash{8%ounce} on a second baking sheet. Sprinkle @chili powder{1%teaspoon} and @cumin{1%teaspoon} evenly over both. Drizzle squash with @honey{1/2%ounce} and sprinkle with as much of the @chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you'd like.

Toss cauliflower and squash with a drizzle of @olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{} each. Roast both veggies in oven until tender and lightly browned, ~{20-25%minutes}, tossing halfway through.

Finely chop @parsley{1/4%ounce}(finely chopped). Cut @lime{1} into wedges. Mince @garlic{1/4%teaspoon}(minced until you have 1/4 tsp).

In a #medium bowl{}, combine @yogurt{1/3%cup}, minced garlic, half the parsley, and a few squeezes of lime (to taste). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Stir in @water{1%tbsp} to give mixture a drizzly consistency.

About 5 minutes before veggies are done roasting, wrap @flour tortillas{6} in #foil{}. Place in oven to warm, about ~{5%minutes}.

> TIP: Alternatively, wrap tortillas in a damp paper towel and microwave on high until warm, about 30 seconds.

Spread yogurt crema onto tortillas and fill each with cauliflower and squash. Sprinkle with @feta cheese{1/2%cup} and remaining parsley. Divide between plates and serve with lime wedges for squeezing over.